(13, NULL, 'Mahachaiensi Green', 'bvr-260326-5488-4732', 'DOA [ Dead on arrival policy ] :- The dead fish must stay in original sealed plastic bag only.- Seller not responsibility if the bag is opened.- Buyers can request a refund the fish\'s cost only but no shipping cost refund and no replacement- Please send a', 'You need to pay the shipping fee twice:\r\nThe first shipping fee within Thailand.(It has already been recorded in the eBay system.)\r\nThe second shipping fee within your country, which will be determined by the local carrier or transhipper in your country.\r\nDear Valued Customer,\r\nWe are delighted to have earned your trust in purchasing betta fish from us. To ensure the utmost safety of your fish during transit, special care is required as cold temperatures can pose a significant risk to betta fish, which thrive in tropical environments. Below are the details of the associated costs:\r\nImport Fee: Approximately $3 per fish\r\nInsulated Box: Approximately $8 per shipment\r\nHeat Pack: Approximately $3 per shipment\r\nDomestic Shipping (UPS 2-Day): Approximately $26 per shipment\r\nTotal Estimated Cost: Approximately $40 per shipment\r\nNote: Shipping costs may vary depending on your country or state.\r\nPlease verify additional shipping costs with your local courier.\r\nTo ensure transparency and accuracy in shipping costs, we recommend contacting your local shipping provider before placing an order. Actual shipping costs may be lower than our initial estimate.\r\nOrder Cancellation Policy\r\nOnce your order has been marked as shipped, cancellation is no longer possible as the fish will already be in transit.\r\nIf you have any questions or need further clarification, please don\'t hesitate to contact us. We are happy to assist you at no extra cost.\r\nThank you for choosing us for your betta fish purchase.\r\n**Once you order a betta fish from us, if the item has been marked as shipped, you wont be able to cancel the order because the fish is already in transit.**\r\nFree Shipping it\'s mean Free of charge From Thailand Shipping Center To US Shipping Center\r\n \"The shipping of betta fish incurs costs in the destination country. Please contact the betta fish sender in your country.\"\r\nYou need to pay the shipping fee twice:\r\nThe first shipping fee within Thailand.(It has already been recorded in the eBay system.)\r\nThe second shipping fee within your country, which will be determined by the local carrier or transhipper in your country.\r\nDear Valued Customer,\r\nWe are delighted to have earned your trust in purchasing betta fish from us. To ensure the utmost safety of your fish during transit, special care is required as cold temperatures can pose a significant risk to betta fish, which thrive in tropical environments. Below are the details of the associated costs:\r\nImport Fee: Approximately $3 per fish\r\nInsulated Box: Approximately $8 per shipment\r\nHeat Pack: Approximately $3 per shipment\r\nDomestic Shipping (UPS 2-Day): Approximately $26 per shipment\r\nTotal Estimated Cost: Approximately $40 per shipment\r\nNote: Shipping costs may vary depending on your country or state.\r\nPlease verify additional shipping costs with your local courier.\r\nTo ensure transparency and accuracy in shipping costs, we recommend contacting your local shipping provider before placing an order. Actual shipping costs may be lower than our initial estimate.\r\nOrder Cancellation Policy\r\nOnce your order has been marked as shipped, cancellation is no longer possible as the fish will already be in transit.\r\nIf you have any questions or need further clarification, please don\'t hesitate to contact us. We are happy to assist you at no extra cost.\r\nThank you for choosing us for your betta fish purchase.\r\n**Once you order a betta fish from us, if the item has been marked as shipped, you wont be able to cancel the order because the fish is already in transit.**\r\nFree Shipping it\'s mean Free of charge From Thailand Shipping Center To US Shipping Center\r\n \"The shipping of betta fish incurs costs in the destination country. Please contact the betta fish sender in your country.\"\r\n Fish ordering / Delivery method:\r\nYou must use transhipper because you don\'t have license to import living\'s form (fish).\r\nI can\'t send fish directly to you, so I send it to transhipper.\r\nSelect transhipper from below list.\r\nThere are  trans-shippers in the USA\r\nTucky Hama                                  California\r\nEdy Tamtama                                NJ\r\nSher Vang                                     MN\r\nJoel Fernandez                             TX\r\nIvan Ramirez                                 FL\r\nEU And etc.\r\n**For the country that is not in the list or you can not search contact from internet, please contact me.**\r\n(eBay\'s policy not allows me to show contact to you)\r\n- I will confirm my shipping date to transhipper.\r\n(Fish\'s shipping frequency is weekly or 1-2 times per month depend on transhipper)\r\n-. After fish is shipped, I\'ll inform you.\r\n-. Because Ebay policy I have to set shipping service to One-day shipping.\r\nIf you have any question, feel free to contact me.\r\nIMPORTANT PLEASE READ SHIPPING METHOD BEFORE PLACE ORDER.  IF YOU BUY THIS BETTA & TROPICAL FISH, THAT MEAN YOU UNDERSTAND AND ACCEPT MY SHIPPING POLICY. \r\n Shipping Info :\r\n We will shipped the Tropical fish to Trans-shippers in the USA every 2-4 weeks.\r\nPlease contact us shipper for information about shipping cost and take the fish.\r\nIt will take another 1-2 days to get from US Shipping Center to your address, and additional\r\nBut different PLEASE!!!\r\n(eBay\'s policy not allows me to show contact to you)\r\nWe will send you the transhipper information Name, location, Phone Number and email, also\r\nand the transhipper contact to you when your order is arrived too. Please send your\r\ncomplete Address , phone number and active email. We will not refund , when your fish arrived\r\nyour country, But if you do not respond to emails from Transhipper , Because your fish\r\nshipped out of Thailand, then it means. We pay for the charge from Thailand Transhipper too.\r\nDOA [ Dead on arrival policy ] :\r\n- The dead fish must stay in original sealed plastic bag only.\r\n- Seller not responsibility if the bag is opened.\r\n- Buyers can request a refund the fish\'s cost only but no shipping cost refund and no replacement\r\n- Please send a clear picture of the DOA fish while the plastic bag has not opened to me.\r\n   If you CAN NOT provide those conditions, we WILL NOT replace or refund.\r\n  POLICY :\r\nBuyer is responsible for knowing the local laws of their country/state/city/etc., as we are not responsible for shipping prohibited products or fish, which may be subject to confiscation from customs. Absolutely no refund will be given in these situations.\r\n* Colors may slightly vary from screen to screen *\r\nWE HAVE OUR OWN FARM TO SERVICE YOU FOR WHOLESALE ORDER.\r\nshould understand before buying\r\nWild betta fish are betta fish that are specialized in shape and habits. Farmers should understand the nature of betta fish well before raising them.\r\n1. Betta fish color will not be available when moving or changing the breeding environment. It takes about 5-15 days for the fish to adjust and the color of the fish will return to its original state.\r\n2. This betta is a warm-water fish. must be raised using a heater when the weather is cold\r\n3. Wild betta fish are very easily startled. When shocked, the fish color will not be there. Or the color of the fish will disappear naturally and will return as much as before when the shock is gone.\r\n4. Wild bettas are bettas that hold peace and quiet. Because it\'s a very easy fish to catch.\r\n5.To raise wild betta fish, you should add Indian almond leaves to the water. The leaves release tannins and other beneficial substances that help the fish feel more comfortable, mimicking their natural environment. This adjustment can help them adapt better, and it may even enhance their colors.\r\n\"Important Note on Fish Color:\r\nThe fish appears blue in the photos because we used a DSLR camera, which can sometimes distort the colors. The fish’s natural color is actually green. However, due to the way light passes through the DSLR lens and the adjustments the camera makes, the fish appears blue in the images. Please be aware that the true color of the fish is green.\"\r\nshould understand before buying\r\nBetta fish are betta fish that are specialized in shape and habits. Farmers should understand the nature of betta fish well before raising them.\r\n1. Betta fish color will not be available when moving or changing the breeding environment. It takes about 5-15 days for the fish to adjust and the color of the fish will return to its original state.\r\n2. This betta is a warm-water fish. must be raised using a heater when the weather is cold\r\n3. Betta fish are very easily startled. When shocked, the fish color will not be there. Or the color of the fish will disappear naturally and will return as much as before when the shock is gone.\r\n4. Bettas are bettas that hold peace and quiet. Because it\'s a very easy fish to catch.\r\n5.To raise Betta fish, you should add Indian almond leaves to the water. The leaves release tannins and other beneficial substances that help the fish feel more comfortable, mimicking their natural environment. This adjustment can help them adapt better, and it may even enhance their colors.\r\nWe are a premier store specializing in Betta fish and Betta fish accessories, located in Chiang Mai, Northern Thailand. With over 10 years of experience in the industry, we offer a wide selection of Betta fish of all breeds, ensuring our customers receive only the best.\r\nAs an esteemed member of the Thailand Betta Fish Network and the Northern Thailand Betta Fish Community, we have earned a reputation for excellence. Over the years, we have expanded into a fully certified Betta fish breeding farm the only export-standard facility in Northern Thailand.\r\nOur commitment to quality and innovation allows us to produce and supply world-class Betta fish in large quantities to international markets. Whether you are a collector, breeder, or enthusiast, we guarantee premium-quality Betta fish that meet the highest global standards.', 'Betta', 'Mahachainensis', NULL, NULL, NULL, 'unknown', NULL, NULL, 'Normal', 29.00, 'USD', 'Thailand', 'Chiang Mai', 'hidden', 'fixed', 0, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 0, NULL, NULL, 'available', 10, 1, 9, NULL, NULL, NULL, 0, '/uploads/listings/13/cover_20260326_195558_54acb8c70594.jpg', 'Betta Live Fighting Fish Wild Mahachaiensis Color Green Male', 'Betta Live Fighting Fish Wild Mahachaiensis Color Green Male', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 0.0000, 0, 0, NULL, NULL, '2026-03-26 19:55:58', '2026-04-11 18:08:23'),
(14, 5, 'Mahachaiensis Betta', 'mah-260330-8836-6842', 'Wild bettas embody the pure, original lineage of the species—refined by nature, not human selection. Sensitive and deeply connected to their natural environment, they require calm, stable conditions and knowledgeable care.\r\nA true choice for collectors wh', 'Wild betta fish represent the original lineage of the species—untouched by selective breeding and deeply rooted in their natural heritage. Each individual carries the authenticity of its origin, shaped by generations in quiet, tannin-rich waters and delicate ecosystems that demand balance and stability.\r\nUnlike fancy bettas, wild bettas retain their instinctive sensitivity. They respond quickly to environmental changes, noise, and stress, requiring conditions that closely mirror their natural habitat. A calm setting, soft lighting, and consistent water parameters are not luxuries, but fundamental necessities for their survival and well-being.\r\nKeeping a wild betta is not a casual pursuit. It is a refined practice that calls for patience, discipline, and respect for nature. We strongly encourage all collectors to study their behavioral patterns and ecological needs in depth before making a selection.\r\nTo choose a wild betta is to honor its lineage—to preserve not only its physical form, but the spirit of the environment from which it came. This is more than ownership; it is stewardship of a living heritage.', 'Betta splendens', 'Mahachaiensis', NULL, NULL, NULL, 'unknown', NULL, NULL, 'Normal', 39.00, 'USD', 'Thailand', 'Chiang Mai', 'active', 'fixed', 0, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 0, NULL, NULL, 'available', 50, 21, 29, NULL, NULL, NULL, 0, '/uploads/listings/14/seller_14_20260330180927_7f47cfb469ce.jpg', 'Buy Wild Betta Fish from Thailand | Rare & Natural Species', 'Discover rare wild betta fish from Thailand. Authentic natural lineage, carefully selected and safely prepared for international collectors worldwide.', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 0.0000, 0, 0, NULL, NULL, '2026-03-30 18:09:27', '2026-05-02 19:43:35'),
(15, 6, 'Smaregdina Betta', 'sma-260330-4653-8045', 'A true wild lineage—pure, sensitive, and preserved for those who understand its value.', 'Wild bettas embody the pure, original lineage of the species—refined by nature, not human selection. Sensitive and deeply connected to their natural environment, they require calm, stable conditions and knowledgeable care.\r\nA true choice for collectors who value authenticity, heritage, and respect for nature.', 'Betta splendens', '35', NULL, NULL, NULL, 'unknown', NULL, NULL, 'Normal', 0.50, 'USD', 'Thailand', 'Chiang Mai', 'hidden', 'fixed', 0, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 0, NULL, NULL, 'available', 350, 106, 244, NULL, NULL, NULL, 1, '/uploads/listings/15/seller_15_20260330230321_a4dc5bbdf05f.jpg', 'Wild Betta Fish for Sale | Rare Natural Betta from Thailand', 'Discover rare wild betta fish from Thailand. Authentic natural lineage, carefully selected and safely prepared for international collectors worldwide.', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 0.0000, 0, 0, NULL, NULL, '2026-03-30 23:03:21', '2026-05-16 20:21:19'),
